@YorickPeterse The aws-sdk-resources gem had never made a stable release when this was removed. It was being published with a ".preview" on the gem version. This required users to opt-into a specific version, ensuring they would not update without changing their dependency.

The change was added to the release notes, changelog and the upgrading document. Additionally, it was made intentionally to avoid a breaking change in the stable version. The plan is to add this back in the future, based on feedback from the SQS service team and pending. Even then it will return with a different interface. 

It would be possible to vendor the existing model and to force this interface for users wanting to upgrade now without changes.

